        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: preserve Feishu post line breaks",
        "body": "Closes #97074\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where users sending Feishu post/markdown messages with ordinary single newlines would see those lines collapsed together as cramped text instead of readable separated lines.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nFeishu post `md` elements need single prose line breaks materialized before payload creation, while fenced code blocks need their original single newlines preserved. The send and edit paths also resolve the Feishu text limit and skip materialization when the rendered post would exceed that limit, so existing chunked callers do not start sending oversized messages.\n\n## User Impact\n\nFeishu post replies with normal multiline prose render with the intended spacing. Code blocks remain compact, and near-limit messages keep the existing bounded send behavior instead of being expanded past the configured Feishu limit.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/feishu/src/send.test.ts extensions/feishu/src/outbound.test.ts extensions/feishu/src/send-target.test.ts extensions/feishu/src/send.reply-fallback.test.ts -- --reporter=dot` (86 tests passed)\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check extensions/feishu/src/send-target.ts extensions/feishu/src/send-result.ts extensions/feishu/src/send.ts extensions/feishu/src/post-markdown.ts extensions/feishu/src/outbound.ts extensions/feishu/src/send.test.ts extensions/feishu/src/outbound.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main --codex-bin .artifacts/codex-flex` (clean, confidence 0.84)\n\nKnown proof gap: I did not run a live Feishu API send because this workspace does not have approved live Feishu credentials for this issue sweep.\n",
